    {
      "id": "graph-organization-overview",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Graph Organization Law",
      "position": {
        "x": -80,
        "y": -140
      },
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "width": 560,
      "height": 240,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Graph Organization Law\n\nBefore leaning harder on templates and galleries, we need practical composition rules so graphs stay readable as they grow.\n\nThis is not math for its own sake. It is authoring law:\n- how sections form\n- what edges mean\n- what canonical graph shapes exist\n- how a graph grows without collapsing into noise",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
